## Migration Tips: Triple Whale to Any Alternative

### Before You Switch

1. **Export your data** — Download historical reports from Triple Whale
2. **Document your setup** — UTM conventions, conversion events, attribution windows
3. **Note your baselines** — Current ROAS by channel for comparison

### During Transition

1. **Run parallel** — Keep Triple Whale active for 4-6 weeks alongside new tool
2. **Compare outputs** — See where attribution differs and investigate why
3. **Test different models** — Compare how credit shifts under First Touch vs Last Touch vs Linear

### After Transition

1. **Remove Triple Whale pixel** — Once confident in new tool
2. **Update team dashboards** — Retrain on new interface
3. **Adjust expectations** — Attribution may look different; neither is "wrong"

